<br>
As far as I can tell, HP are the only thing not capped, or rather without an additional cap.  If you mean HP are capped because there are 18 slots that can each hold no more than 125 +HP, then sure.  But Mana has an additional cap beyond that of either +1400 (FoH emperical testing) or +1425 (Lotusfly stated figure).<br>
<br>
&quot;Does the mana cap include buffs that are cast upon you? (ie you have 4250 mana without buffs, but when you get KEI you have 4250+ Kei, or is it still 4250?&quot;<br>
<br>
The cap is only a cap on +mana gained from items, not a limit on the total size of your mana pool.  That is what Lotusfly said and that is what the FoH emperical testing has shown so far. <p>____________<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13463"
